sentences: Ahmed Soultan (أحمد سلطان; born June 17, 1978) is a Moroccan singer artist, considered one of the leaders of the "Nayda".(new urban Moroccan scene).
His 1st album "Tolerance" (2005), which contains his first single "Ya Salam".
And then his 2nd album "Code" (2009) which contains the 1st extract "Achkide".
After a second album, released in 2009, in which he asserts himself, his popularity in and over the Maghreb was confirmed.

He became involved in various projects : he wrote the original soundtrack of Rhimou, a successful sitcom broadcast in Morocco and more ; he collaborated with the famous American singer Ne-Yo, on a song called "Amazing You" ; in 2011, his song "Jokko" was nominated as best North African song and best African reggae song of the year.
